Subtitle Editor is a GTK+2 tool to edit subtitles for GNU/Linux/*BSD.
It can be used for new subtitles or as a tool to transform, edit,
correct and refine existing subtitle. This program also shows sound
waves, which makes it easier to synchronise subtitles to voices.

Subtitle Editor needs the following dependencies (listed in build order), 
all of which are available at SlackBuilds.org:

enchant, liboil, gstreamer, gst-plugins-base, gst-ffmpeg, gst-plugins-good,
gst-plugins-bad, gst-plugins-ugly, libsigc++, glibmm, cairomm, gtkmm, 
libglademm, and libxml++.
